Anabrolepis extranea

; 

Yasumatsu & Tachikawa (
1949
)

; 

Ishii (
1928
)

; 
Tachikawa (1955
, 
1974
).

Head. Frontovertex at anterior ocellus 1 / 5 − 1 / 4 head width; ocelli forming an angle of 45 º − 60 º; posterior ocellus about half its own diameter from inner eye margin, and separated from occiptal margin by 3−4 × its own diameter; antennal scape about 2.7 × as long as wide; F 1 −F 4 transverse, smaller than F 5 and F 6 (
Fig. 61
); mandible with two teeth and an upper truncation.

Thorax. Fore wing (
Fig. 62
) about 2.3 × as long as broad; marginal vein about as long as stigmal vein; postmarginal vein short or nearly absent.

Gaster. Ovipositor sheaths (
Fig. 64
) slightly exserted, by about 1 / 7 gaster length.
